summary:
Experienced HR professional with 25+ years experience as HR Generalist in the Energy sector, led major change initiatives as part of Shell's global Diversity and Inclusion team. CHRP(Canada) and CIPD ( UK) professionally accredited. Myers Briggs/I-OPT/Kantor accredited practitioner. International experience; USA, Canada, UK, Syria, NL, supporting European, Middle East and North American regional businesses. Key knowledge areas: Diversity and Inclusion strategy and program management, HR Business Partnering, HR Policy and Compensation, Org Effectiveness/Change and Project management, Leadership Development, Talent management. Experienced HR leader, having led teams for 10 years+.
Most recent key role was in Shell's global Diversity & Inclusion team, providing support to business and country leadership and HR teams, as well as to employee networks and D&I champions. This included advising them as they executed their plans to attract, retain and develop talented people from diverse backgrounds, and working together to deliver policy and culture change programs with the intent of building a more inclusive work environment for all staff at Shell.
